               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18361128-223-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-223-18361128 t18361128-223-offence-1 t18361128-223-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>223. <persName id="def1-223-18361128" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-223-18361128" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-223-18361128" type="age" value="21"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-223-18361128" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-223-18361128" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN SMITH</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18361128-223-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18361128-223-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18361128-223-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp> for a misdemeanor.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1509" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1509" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1509" type="surname" value="CARELESS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1509" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY CARELESS</persName>
                  </hi>. My husband keeps a shop in Robert-street, North Brixton, and sells tripe. On the 12th of November the prisoner came there, and bought 1/2lb. of sausages—he gave me a shilling—I gave him 9 1/2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—I said, "I do not like this shilling, I do not think it is good"—he said, "I wish I had one more than I could carry"—he went out, and I looked at it again, and found it was bad—I put it into a tea-pot on a shelf, and kept it till I gave it to Mr. Slaughter—there was no other with it—on the 14th of November, about nine o'clock in the morning, the prisoner came again for a red herring, which I put on the counter—he tendered another shilling—I saw it was the same sort of coin as he had given me before—I said I could not give him change—he said he would get change—I then sent for a policeman—Slaughter came before the prisoner was out of sight—I gave him the shilling I first took, after I had marked it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1510" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1510" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1510" type="surname" value="MARTIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1510" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MARTIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Bromley-row, Clapham, and sell shoemaker's materials. The prisoner came on the 14th of November about a quarter after ten o'clock for a pennyworth of nails, and gave me a bad shilling, I gave him 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—while I was serving, he amused me with a tale of his having some onions to sell—I said I wanted none that prevented me from noticing the shilling so much as I might—I put it into my pocket—I had there two sixpences, and another shilling, a new one, which I had taken three quarters of an hour before—the shilling the prisoner gave me was the coin of George III—I had it in my pocket about two days—I soon after saw Slaughter—I did not give him the shilling till ordered by the Magistrate.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1511" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1511" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1511" type="surname" value="SLAUGHTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1511" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE SLAUGHTER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable P</hi> 152.) In consequence of what Mrs. Careless said, I went after the prisoner—I first saw him in the Clap<lb></lb>ham-road—I saw him go to Mr. Martin's shop—I waited till the came out, and took him—Mr. Martin gave me this shilling—I searched the prisoner, and found two good sixpences and 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in copper—I told the prisoner I had got something else against him, for passing a shilling to Mrs. Careless—he said he had not been that road that day that he came from Wandsworth—I took him to the station-house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I told you I had been to Martin's; and when you got to the door you said I had not been in there—I said I had, and I would go in—and he pulled out the two shillings, and said he did not know which I gave him—you</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183611280240"></xptr>
               <p>weighed them, and found one bad, and then said it must be the bad one I gave him. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> He pulled out two shillings, and I said, "Which is the one gave you?"—he said, "This is the one"—an then he took and put a shilling in one scale and the other in the other, and found it was bad—I never saw the prisoner till I found him in the Clapham-road—I fol<lb></lb>lowed him most of the way from Mr. Careless's—I saw him enter the shop at the front—I did not know then that it was Mr. Martin's—I followed him from Brixton to Clapham—I had not lost sight of him above two minutes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. FIELD</hi>. These are both counterfeit, and from the same die.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18361128-223-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-223-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-223-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 21.—
<rs id="t18361128-223-punishment-206" type="punishmentDescription">
